*: A styled registration form using Bootstrap Input Groups, Font Awesome icons, and CSS Flexbox for a two-column layout. The form includes fields for Name, Email, Phone, City, and Address.\n4. **Footer.jsx**: A full-width Bootstrap footer.\n\nThe `css` folder contains `registration_form.css` for custom styling, including background colors, dimensions, borders, and box shadows for the registration form. All components are imported and rendered in `App.jsx` in the following order: Header, Accordion, RegistrationForm, and Footer.','assignment'),(100,'2026-04-06 16:16:51.973769','rose@gmail.com','**Summary:**\n\nThe **Second Assignment** for the **BCA (Bachelor of Computer Applications)** program, **Year 3, Semester 6**, focuses on the course **Basics of Cloud Computing (Course Code: CA333)** for the academic year **2025-26**. The assignment is due on **06/04/2026** and carries a maximum of **10 marks**, with each of the **5 compulsory questions** worth **2 marks**. The submission must be **handwritten on A4 pages**.\n\n**Key Topics Covered:**  \n1. **Interoperability, Portability, and Scalability**: Their roles in cloud computing and impact on business operations.  \n2. **Cloud Solution Selection**: Critical factors like security, scalability, and cost.  \n3. **Cloud Contracting Models**: Their significance in addressing legal and commercial aspects of cloud adoption.  \n4. **Legal Challenges in Cloud Computing**: Issues related to data privacy, security, and jurisdiction.  \n5. **Cloud Governance**: Definition and the necessity of IT governance in cloud computing.  \n\nThe assignment aligns with specific **Bloom’s Taxonomy (BT)**, **Course Outcomes (CO)**, and **Program Outcomes (PO)** to assess understanding of foundational and advanced cloud computing concepts.','ax'),(101,'2026-04-06 16:23:13.159882','rose@gmail.com','The **BCA** program\'s **second assignment** for the **3rd year/6th semester** in the **2025-26** academic year focuses on the **Basics of Cloud Computing** (**CA333**). Due on **06/04/2026**, this **10-mark** assignment requires **handwritten A4 submissions** with **compulsory answers** to five questions, each worth **2 marks**. Key topics include the role of **interoperability**, **portability**, and **scalability** in cloud computing (**Q.1**), **critical considerations** for selecting cloud solutions like **security**, **scalability**, and **cost** (**Q.2**), **cloud contracting models** and their legal/commercial significance (**Q.3**), **legal challenges** such as **data privacy**, **security**, and **jurisdictional issues** (**Q.4**), and the definition and necessity of **cloud governance** in **IT governance** (**Q.5**).','ax'),(102,'2026-04-06 16:29:40.331656','rose@gmail.com','The assignment requires building a **React** application named `third_app` with a structured folder organization, including `components` and `css` directories. The app features four key components: a **Bootstrap Navbar** (`Header.jsx`), a **Bootstrap Accordion** (`Accordion.jsx`), a styled **registration form** (`RegistrationForm.jsx`) using **Bootstrap**, **Font Awesome**, and **Flexbox**, and a **Bootstrap footer** (`Footer.jsx`). The registration form includes fields for **Name**, **Email**, **Phone**, **City**, and **Address**, styled with **custom CSS**. All components are imported and rendered in `App.jsx` in the order: **Header**, **Accordion**, **RegistrationForm**, and **Footer**.','hello'),(103,'2026-04-06 16:30:54.423925','rose@gmail.com','The assignment requires building a **React** application named `third_app` with a structured folder organization, including `components` and `css` directories. The app features four key components: a **Bootstrap Navbar** (`Header.jsx`), a **Bootstrap Accordion** (`Accordion.jsx`), a styled **registration form** (`RegistrationForm.jsx`) using **Bootstrap**, **Font Awesome**, and **Flexbox**, and a **Bootstrap footer** (`Footer.jsx`). The registration form includes fields for **Name**,